BioDavid P. Petersen has earned the prestigious recognition of being Board Certified in Personal Injury Trial Law by the Texas State Bar Board of Specialization and has been in private practice in the Houston area since 1992. He has extensive experience in virtually all aspects of personal injury and consumer protection litigation, from beginning to final resolution of your case.Focus and attention is made to resolve each client’s case efficiently and prior to the necessity of filing a lawsuit. In those cases where a lawsuit is required, clients are kept well informed of the status of their case and through its preparation for trial. If trial becomes inevitable, parties and their witnesses will be thoroughly prepared to testify. With attention to detail, clients become familiar with the process and thereby feel more comfortable in an adversarial setting which gives them the needed confidence to tell their story with sound credibility.In the rare case where an appeal is taken after a trial, David P. Petersen continues to represent his clients, having enjoyed a highly successful appeal track record.If you are looking for an attorney who will protect your legal rights while paying attention to detail and who is available to discuss your case at any stage, please consider allowing The Law Offices of David P. Petersen, P.C., review your case with you.Our firm practices on both an hourly and contingency fee basis in which if the case is accepted on contingency, there is no cost to you unless we recover for you. 



 





