Bio


	In 1993 David M. Peterson founded Peterson & Associates, P.C.™
	 a highly aggressive and successful plaintiffs-only mass tort and
	personal injury law firm that handles all types of catastrophic personal injury cases, with an
	 emphasis in the areas of pharmaceutical and medical device litigation.
	 He has obtained well in excess of one million dollars in successful judgments
	 and verdicts. He has collected over $400 million on behalf of his clients.

Mr. Peterson practices from coast-to-coast, and has handled or been involved
	 in cases in over twenty states. Mr. Peterson has been part of many successful
	 mass tort and Multidistrict Court (MDL) litigations, having successfully
	 resolved thousands of cases against pharmaceutical and medical device
	 manufacturers.
He was a partner at the international litigation defense firm Shook, Hardy
	 & Bacon where he practiced law for almost ten years. Prior to founding
	 Peterson & Associates, P.C.™, he defended major corporations
	 against catastrophic complex products liability claims, knowing how major
	 corporations defend themselves creates a tremendous advantage in preparing
	 for trial and shaping plaintiffs’ cases to greatly enhance success at trial.
Mr. Peterson has been voted by his peers to be included in Missouri and
	 Kansas SuperLawyers® for the last three years in a row. He has also
	 been rated by his peers as an A-V lawyer, the very highest rating possible
	 as awarded by Martindale-Hubbell.

