CURRENT AVAILABLE POSITIONS





Automotive Technician II




JOB DESCRIPTION:
Department: Technical-Operations
Reports To: Collections Automotive Technician I
FLSA: Non-exempt
The Petersen Automotive Museum is a non-profit organization whose mission is to explore and present the history of the automobile and its impact on American life and culture using Los Angeles as the prime example. Located in the heart of Los Angeles’ Miracle Mile district, the Petersen Automotive Museum is one of the world’s largest and most innovative automotive museums. The Petersen has three floors of 25 exhibits, including The Mechanical Institute Discovery Center.
Position Summary
The duties of the Collections Technician II are focused on assisting with the long-term care, maintenance and preservation of collections vehicles and related objects. The Collections Technician II will assist with the preservation and maintenance program, participate in researching appropriate preservation and maintenance methods, assist with preserving and maintaining collections objects in accordance with accepted methods, and maintain accurate records of work completed.
Essential Functions


Assist with the preservation, maintenance, restoration, and repair of museum vehicles,   fleet vehicles and related objects
Assist with managing the general maintenance program; perform or assist with maintenance, conservation, restoration, and repair tasks as needed or assigned
Keep records of work performed
Adhere to maintenance requirements for collections vehicles
Report on progress of restoration and maintenance tasks
Maintain contact with select outside contractors hired to perform restoration, maintenance, and preservation tasks as needed or assigned
Assist with light maintenance of loaned vehicles
Participate in the evaluation of potential donations, loans or purchases
Assist in the supervision of volunteers who donate their time toward the maintenance of collection objects
Maintain function and appearance of the Vault area
Assist in the upkeep and disposition of Museum equipment, parts and supplies
Assist with installation and maintenance of exhibit vehicles
Assist with transportation of incoming and outgoing vehicles
Assist with education and other public program activities
Travel with vehicles to represent Museum at select public outreach venues
Assist with special projects as assigned

Other Responsibilities
Perform other work-related duties as assigned
Education, Experience and Skills Required

Bachelor’s degree in Automotive Technology or related field
Minimum ten years experience in hands-on maintenance of similar vehicles

To Apply:  Please email cover letter and resume to  [email protected] with “Automotive Technician II” in subject line.






Visitor Services Representative 




Job Title: Visitor Services Representative
Department: Visitor Services
Report to: Visitor Services Manager
FLSA: Non-Exempt
 
JOB DESCRIPTION:
Position Summary:
The Petersen Automotive Museum currently seeks a Visitor Services Representative (VSR). VSRs actively engage with visitors at the museum’s Admissions Desk. Serving as the face of the museum, VSRs are responsible for processing admissions sales, upselling membership and vault tours, providing visitors with information about exhibitions and upcoming events, and facilitating in providing an overall welcoming environment at the Petersen Automotive Museum. The position requires availability on weekends, holidays, and flexibility to work at museum events. This position is ideal for a recent graduate or current college student seeking entry-level experience in a museum setting.
Essential Functions:

Maintain accurate monetary transactions including fees for admission, advance admission, parking, memberships as well as group/school tours, and gift tickets/cards.
Review daily cash drawer transactions for admissions.
Facilitate the Forza Motorsport Racing Experience gallery and ensure visitors are following the gallery’s policies and rules.
Oversee the VR/Hololens experience.
Conduct museum visitor surveys and collect data / feedback.
Provide helpful and friendly service to visiting museum patrons.
Provide information to the public regarding general information and upcoming events.
Dress in clean and presentable attire comprised of a uniform shirt, comfortable close-toed shoes, and business appropriate pants.
Performs other work-related duties and projects as assigned.

Qualifications

Cashier and Customer Service experience required
AA degree preferred
Excellent communications and interpersonal skills are essential
Prior sales, customer service, hospitality and experience working with the public required
High attention to detail
Ability to commit to a fixed weekly schedule
Be able to work in a fast paced environment

We’re looking for someone who wants to be part of something big and fast-paced, and is ready to hit the ground running. The ideal candidate will be daring enough to provide feedback and ideas that coincide with the forward-thinking practices of the Petersen. 
The Petersen Automotive Museum is a non-profit organization whose mission is to explore and present the history of the automobile and its impact on American life and culture using Los Angeles as a prime example. Located in the heart of Los Angeles’ famed Miracle Mile district, the Petersen Automotive Museum is one of the world’s largest and most innovative automotive museums.
To apply, email a cover letter and resume to the Visitor Services Manager, at [email protected]. Incomplete applications will not be considered. We are regretfully unable to respond to phone calls and emails regarding the status of applications and the recruiting process.





Museum Educator 




JOB DESCRIPTION
Title: Museum Educator
Department: Education
Reports To: Education Manager 
FLSA: Non-exempt/Part-Time
The Petersen Automotive Museum is a non-profit organization whose mission is to explore and present the history of the automobile and its impact on American life and culture using Los Angeles as the prime example. Located in the heart of Los Angeles’ Miracle Mile district, the Petersen Automotive Museum is one of the world’s largest and most innovative automotive museums. The Petersen has three floors of 25 new exhibits, including The Mechanical Institute Discovery Center. The Discovery Center is an exciting, new Cars-themed gallery for visitors of all ages, built in partnership with Disney/Pixar. This interactive gallery immerses children in a hands-on environment in which they learn about the many systems and components that make cars work.
Position Summary 
We are seeking Museum Educators to oversee the daily activity in the Discovery Center gallery by providing responsible, friendly, and enthusiastic assistance to museum visitors, and to lead occasional gallery tours for school groups. S/he will interact with visitors on the floor, facilitate hands-on gallery stations, and foster a welcoming environment for volunteers and the public. S/he will provide customer service support, be knowledgeable about museum content, and will maintain daily gallery operations and appearance.
Essential Functions 
• Assisting visitors with Discovery Center interactive iPad experiences
• Managing the check-out and return of iPads
• Facilitating interactive demonstrations at gallery stations
• Setting up youth and family activity supplies 
• Providing direction and guidance to visitors concerning other galleries
• Working with and mentoring Discovery Center volunteers
• Ensuring that objects and resources are handled carefully and safely
• Maintaining gallery cleaning procedures and ensuring that supplies are replenished
• Performing crowd control during peak times
• Participating in staffing Family Days and other special youth programs as required
• Leading occasional school tours of museum galleries 
Education, Experience and Skills Required:
• At least one year experience working directly with the public 
• Excellent customer service skills
• Experience working with children and families 
• Coursework in museum studies, child development, history, or related field a plus
• Interest in automotive culture and history 
• Experience leading tours or interpreting museum galleries/exhibits desirable 
• Familiarity with informal education techniques 
• Ability to deliver content to audiences of all ages and abilities, and to adapt content for different learning styles 
• Familiarity with technology; ability to work with technology in an educational capacity
• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills
• Ability to work independently as well as in a team environment
• Bilingualism (Spanish) a plus 
• Ability to stand for extended periods of time
Compensation: $12/hour. Maximum 28 hours per week; must be available a minimum of 20 hours per week; must be available to work at least one weekend day, as well as during some holiday and peak periods. 
To apply: Please email cover letter, resume, and three references to [email protected] with “Museum Educator” in subject line.
Resumes without cover letters will not be considered. No calls, please.
Resumes without cover letters will not be considered. No calls, please.





